    "updated_at": "2012-06-04T04:28:28Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The nasty complexity with a config dialog is that ultimately we'll wand that to be persisted (any decent GUI program that has a settings dialog will save your choices).  But some of those options are already in our python config files.  Having GUI-controlled options on top of human-editable-file ones is tricky and unpleasant to deal with.\n\nThis is a bullet we'll need to bite at some point, though I'm not sure now we have the bandwidth for it...\n"
  },
